  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency flood response in Somalia by providing access to clean safe water, sanitation and hygiene services in Gedo, Mudug and Bari regions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of the project is to provide access to clean water, sanitation and hygiene for communities affected by flooding in Gedo, Galmudug and Bari regions. IOM will use CERF funding to rehabilitate and upgrade 15 shallow wells and 4 boreholes, provide aqua tabs for household water treatment, construct 750 latrines with hand washing facilities, distribute 12,000 hygiene kits. In total, the project will target 72,000 displaced persons and persons belonging to host communities, including 40,320 women and girls and 360 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
